Feed post number 11

Ronak Jain contributed to this

Your design consistency is at risk due to missed deadlines. How can you ensure your projects stay on track?

37 expert answers

Ensuring design project consistency

Ronak Jain • Following

🚀Web Developer & Graphic Designer | 10M+ Views👀 | Freelancer | LinkedIn Top Voice | Creating Stunning Websites, Logos & Social Media Graphics for Real Estates, Agencies & Restaurants | Make a Strong Online Brand
To keep design projects on track and maintain consistency:

• Break down tasks: Divide projects into smaller, manageable parts to avoid overwhelm.

• Prioritize time management: Use time-blocking techniques to allocate focused hours for creative work.

• Streamline feedback: Limit revisions by consolidating client feedback into clear action points.

• Automate repetitive tasks: Use templates or automation tools for recurring elements to save time.

What methods do you use to keep your projects efficient? Share your insights!

SHAIKH AAMIR SOHAILSHAIKH AAMIR SOHAIL • 3rd+ • 3rd+ Web developer © Java 8+ | Techweaver |Web developer © Java 8+ | Techweaver | 2d • 2 days ago
‼️Job Interviews!‼️

As a recruiter, I see talented people crash & burn at interviews.

8 Things You Should NEVER Say in a Job Interview
(and exactly what to say instead):

❌ Don’t Say: “I’m looking for good work-life balance.”
🟢 Ask: “What are the key expectations for success here?”
❌ Don’t Say: “I don’t have any questions.”
🟢 Ask: “Tell me more about the team I’d be working with?”
❌ Don’t Say: “I didn’t get along with my last boss.”
🟢 Say: “I’m looking for a work place that values collaboration and respect.”
❌ Don’t Say: “I’ll do anything.”
 🟢 Say: “I’m passionate about [specific area]. How can I contribute to this at your company?”
❌ Don’t Say: “What does this company do again?”
🟢 Say: “I was impressed by [specific project/initiative].”
❌ Don’t Say: “How soon can I get promoted?”
🟢 Ask: “What are the opportunities for growth?”
❌ Don’t Just Say: “I don’t know.”
🟢 Ask: “Can I have some time to check & get back to you?”
❌ Don’t Say: “I’m looking for $X amount of salary.”
🟢 Say: “I’m looking for a reasonable uplift. In terms of exact numbers, let me get back to you.”
Master these and you’ll ace the interview.

When you know what to say,
you're not just a candidate.

You get hired.

On campus job opportunity

The Department of Employee Relations at the University of Pretoria (UP) is recruiting Interns. UP offers this opportunity to candidates seeking practical experience and exposure. This aligns with UP’s ‘Ready for Work’ initiative for UP graduates.

Interns’ responsibilities:
The successful candidates will be placed in the department noted above. In general, the responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Filling
Administration Work
Assist ER Officials

Prior work experience is not required:
All successful candidates will receive training/mentorship; thus, prior work experience is not required.

Benefits of internship:
This opportunity will help all successful candidates when applying for other career opportunities after they complete the programme.

Candidate requirements:
UP bachelor’s degree in human resources or LLB
Languages: English (spoken and written);
Between 18 and 35 of age; and
South African citizen

Additional Application Information:
Applications must be emailed to: Internship@up.ac.za

Documents to include:
Certified ID copy
Academic records/Proof of qualification
5 Ready for Work certificates
Updated CV

Contract Duration: 24 Months
Reference to use in the subject line: “DER-2024”
Closing Date: Sunday the 13th of October 2024
Please note: No late applications will be accepted.

𝗚𝗹𝗼𝗯𝗮𝗹 𝗩𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲𝘀 𝗩𝗦 𝗟𝗼𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗩𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲𝘀

➜ 𝗚𝗹𝗼𝗯𝗮𝗹 𝗩𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲𝘀: These are variables that can be accessed from anywhere in the program. Once declared, a global variable is available across different functions, blocks, or scopes. Think of it as a variable that has a wide reach and can be used or modified by any part of the code.

➜ 𝗟𝗼𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗩𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲𝘀: These are variables that exist only within a specific function, block, or scope. They are declared and used within that specific area and cannot be accessed from outside that scope. Local variables help in keeping data contained, limiting the scope of where they can be modified or accessed.

Global variables have a wider scope and are accessible throughout the entire program, while local variables are confined to a specific part of the code.

𝗜𝗳 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗳𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲, 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗲𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗵𝗶𝘁 "𝗟𝗶𝗸𝗲" 𝗯𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗼𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘀𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗶𝘁 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗻𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸✅

🚀 Master Key JavaScript Concepts for Your Next Interview 🚀

🎯 JavaScript continues to be a crucial skill for developers, and preparing for technical interviews requires in-depth understanding of its core features.

🎯 Here's a quick look at essential topics to brush up on:

📚 Want to ace your next interview? Make sure you’re well-prepared with these fundamental concepts!

Feed post number 59

Java Developers Community (moderated)Java Developers Community (moderated) Shree Ram Sharma • 3rd+Shree Ram Sharma • 3rd+ 2h • 2 hours ago
🚀 Mastering Design Patterns: Turning Chaos into Structured Solutions 🧩

Imagine walking into a restaurant with no menu. The chef prepares random dishes, and you’re left hoping for something good. Chaos, right?
Now imagine the same restaurant with a clear, structured menu—organized, predictable, and efficient. That’s exactly what Design Patterns do for your code. They offer a set of proven solutions to common challenges, ensuring clean, reusable, and scalable code.

🔍 There are 3 main types of design patterns:
1️⃣ Creational Patterns: These focus on how objects are created, ensuring flexibility and reuse.
Examples:
👉 Singleton: Ensures a class has only one instance.
👉 Factory Method: Creates objects without exposing creation logic.
👉 Builder: Constructs complex objects step-by-step.

2️⃣ Structural Patterns: These help in organizing relationships between objects, making large systems easier to manage.
Examples:
👉 Adapter: Bridges interfaces so incompatible classes can work together.
👉 Decorator: Dynamically adds behavior to objects.
👉 Facade: Provides a simple interface to complex subsystems.
👉 Proxy: Controls access to an object, managing its lifecycle.

3️⃣ Behavioral Patterns: These govern how objects communicate and interact, streamlining workflows.
Examples:
👉 Observer: Notifies multiple objects when the state of another object changes.
👉 Strategy: Encapsulates different algorithms and swaps them as needed.
👉 Chain of Responsibility: Passes requests along a chain of handlers.

In short, design patterns are like a roadmap for your code, turning complexity into elegance. Ready to implement them and build scalable systems? 🚀
hashtag#Java hashtag#python hashtag#JavaScript hashtag#DesignPatterns hashtag#CleanCode hashtag#SoftwareEngineering hashtag#Programming hashtag#TechTips

Siphiwe Sitwayi likes this
Idea Citizen (Formerly TED - Unofficial)Idea Citizen (Formerly TED - Unofficial) Anthony Ofili NWOSISI MSc. • 3rd+Anthony Ofili NWOSISI MSc. • 3rd+
View my services
5h • 5 hours ago
“Thermal drones – modern marvels, redefining what is possible when humanity and technology converge in moments of critical need. In Alto, Wisconsin, when a three-year-old boy was lost amidst towering cornfields, it was not mere human intuition or daylight search parties that found him. It was a thermal drone – an eye in the sky – leveraging the power of infrared to pierce the darkness and find life where otherwise there was only obscurity. The drone’s heat-signature technology cut through the dense field, swiftly locating the boy and delivering him to safety. In a world where minutes can mean the difference between life and tragedy, technology’s intervention is not just helpful – it’s heroic.

But we must think deeper. This instance is more than just a localized success; it’s an embodiment of how cutting-edge tech reshapes our world. The profound implications of AI-augmented thermal drones extend far beyond rescue missions. Imagine the power of combining AI’s data analytics capabilities with robotics, and thermal vision – a trifecta that brings unparalleled precision. AI algorithms could autonomously direct drones to optimize search patterns, predict movement based on terrain and weather conditions, and even adapt dynamically as a situation unfolds.

Such technology doesn’t just find; it learns. And as it learns, it could transform sectors – from disaster response and firefighting, where navigating through smoke and debris is paramount, to wildlife conservation, silently monitoring endangered species at night without disturbance. The possibilities are as vast as the skies themselves.

The fusion of AI, robotics, and thermal imaging isn’t just a trend – it’s the dawn of a new era where humanity extends its reach through the hands and eyes of machines, making the unseen seen, and the unreachable within grasp. And in doing so, we’re not just solving problems; we’re redefining how we understand and interact with our world. The future of search and rescue, law enforcement, and environmental protection looks brighter – and warmer – through the lens of thermal drones.”

hashtag#ThermalDrones hashtag#AI hashtag#Robotics hashtag#Innovation hashtag#SearchAndRescue hashtag#TechnologyForGood hashtag#AIForHumanity

JavaScriptJavaScript Youcef Slimani • 3rd+Youcef Slimani • 3rd+ 8h • 8 hours ago
In teamwork, silence isn’t golden; it’s deadly. A supportive team is the key to successl👌

Below how to build strong development team :

👉 Build trust: Foster openness and vulnerability among team members.

👉 Embrace conflict: Encourage constructive discussions to resolve disagreements.

👉 Commit to decisions: Ensure everyone supports team decisions once made.

👉 Focus on collective goals: Prioritize team goals over individual interests.

👉 Clarify roles: Make sure everyone knows their role and responsibilities.

👉 Encourage dialogue: Maintain open, continuous communication.

👉 Resolve issues fast: Address conflicts before they escalate.

👉 Promote responsibility: Ensure accountability for actions and outcomes.

👉 Practice active listening: Make sure everyone feels heard and understood.

👉 Share knowledge: Encourage team members to share insights and expertise.

👉 Foster a supportive environment: Create a culture where team members help each other

👉 Lead by example: Leaders should model the desired behaviors.
